The paper deals with object detection, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed approach involves machine learning techniques such as group recursive learning and multi-stage architecture, which are often used in the subfields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of weakly-supervised object segmentation cues, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
